We’re one week into the fall semester, and we’re so happy to have our #OUFamily on campus! In order to have a healthy year together, the university strongly recommends and encourages healthy behaviors and masking to the entirety of our OU community. 

Hear a message from OU President Harroz on the importance of masking on campus, especially in classrooms, to ensure we have a successful year and stay #OUTogether.

Learn more by visiting ou.edu/together

Today is National Book Lovers Day and a great time to get acquainted with one of the most iconic locations on OU Norman’s campus. 📚

It was a weekend full of celebration, families, and honoring the hard work of our students as they transition to #OUalumni. We’re still not over it. 

No matter where life takes you next, remember you’ll always have a home at the University of Oklahoma. Congratulations, 2020 & 2021 graduates! We are proud of you. ❤️🎓☝🏼

As we prepare to celebrate and honor our graduates in the Classes of 2020 and 2021 this weekend, we take time to reflect on a year unlike any other.

This journey has given us a new perspective, but our goal remains the same - to live out what it means to be part of the #OUFamily and to do so together. Live On, 2021. ☝🏼

As the spring 2021 semester comes to an end, we express our sincerest gratitude to the OU community for overcoming all the challenges that have tried to detour us, remaining diligent and flexible, and for sticking together during the toughest of times. 

Thank you to our OU family. This semester was possible because of you. Live On, University! ☝🏼

node.text:
Welcome to your first day of the fall semester, OU! We are thrilled to welcome you back, and now more than ever is the time to protect yourself and your community to ensure we have a safe and healthy semester ahead. 

▫️ Make plans to attend OU’s vaccine clinic on the OU-Norman campus and get vaccinated 
▫️ Wear a mask indoors and in high-density areas 
▫️ Practice healthy behaviors like washing your hands and staying home if you feel sick 
▫️ Download the OU Healthy Together App to monitor your health before you come to campus 

Let’s have a great year, OU! By working together to slow the spread of COVID-19, we can stay #OUTogether.
